## Contest Model Architecture (System 1)

Based on academic literature: TradingAgents team-based contest, PolySwarm Bayesian aggregation, Hidden Strength of Disagreement (implicit consensus outperforms explicit in volatile markets).

Each cycle:
1. Each Misfit independently generates their best trade signal from their own data
2. Each signal scored: Risk/Reward x Environment Weight x Bayesian Win Rate x Confidence
3. Highest scoring signal executes -- no veto, no consensus required
4. Co-signals on same asset or theme boost position size
5. Quarter-Kelly sizing with multipliers for confidence and co-signals

Minimum bar for execution: contest score above 1.5 AND risk reward above 2.0

